title: For Sale:  Russain Mosin Nagant 91/30 Manufactured 1943
postcontent:
Russian Mosin Nagant 91/30

I have a Mosin Nagant I am looking to sell.  It comes with sling, dual oil/solvent bottle, cleaning rod, cleaning kit, multitool, pouch for the kit, twin ammo pouch, and bayonet 

I have a rubber buttstock add on that will go with it as well (shown in picture).  I will remount the original before selling.  And 8 stripper clips + 40 rounds of 7.62x54r, which is enough to fill the ammo pouches.

I'm not a huge surplus guy, but if you have questions let me know and I will try to look them up.  Manufacturers date is 1943, so it is a WWII model, and while the manufacturers hallmark is kind of faint, I believe it is a Izhevsk model.  I don't know how they rate these surplus guns, but my personal rating would be good, its not pristine, but looks decent enough and shoots well enough that I was happy with it the way it was.

I've gone through the tedious process of getting all the cosmoline (or what ever the russians call theirs) off of the rifle, to include the chamber, so it doesn't get sticky after a few rounds.

I've taken this out shooting probably three times, shoots well enough with iron sights, but I cheated on my other Mosin and have mounted a scout scope so I can see out a bit farther.  They shot roughly the same before the scope, but I think I am more consistent with the scope on the other one now.  So this one is a bit of a duplicate for me.

I not much interested in a trade, but I might consider trading this Mosin Nagant for a Hex Receiver model, or a Russian Carbine model, since that would allow me to have a iron sight mosin that wasn't such a clone of what I already have.

Based on my read of the new law, this falls in the category of old enough to not have to bother with the mandatory background checks.  If you believe differently, please include the text of the bill that passed the legislature and highlight the relevant portion.  Sale would be face to face with Colorado ID, in Monument, or far north end of Colorado springs.  Preference to LEO or Colorado Conceal carry holders.

title: For Sale:  Italian Vetterli Vitali 1870/87/15 plus Ammo
postcontent: Italian Vetterli-Vitali 1870/87/15. A little history... this was originally a single shot rifle that shot a black powder 10.4 mm cartridge. A repeater magazine was added in 1887, but these were replaced by the M91 Carcano in the 1890's. In World War I, there was a shortage of rifles, so the Vetterli-Vitali's were sleeved to shoot the 6.5 mm Carcano round, and were given to reserve and home guard troops. This rifle looks to have had the stock refinished, but some of the cartouche is barely visible. I have not fired this rifle. It is from the Torri Annuziata arsenal and is dated 1889, making it an antique. I will include 50 rounds of 6.5 Carcano ammo. $325 OBO.

title: For Sale:  AK-47 Milled Receiver and Barrel
postcontent:
The AK-47 milled receiver and barrel from Liberty Arms International in Victoria, Texas. Milled from a solid block of 4140 steel, milled receiver includes a rear trunnion as well as pre-drilled holes for the axis pins and the selector switch. 

The barrels are manufactured by O.F. Mossberg & Sons, better known as Mossberg. Barrel comes with a pre-drilled hole for the gas port as well as pre-cut notches for the handguard. 

The AK-47 milled receiver and barrel is "in the white," meaning that they have yet to be finished with any sort of treatment for resistance to corrosion, pitting or wear. This allows you to finish your receiver and barrel in any manner you want, whether it be bluing, parkerizing, Molykoting® or anything else you deem fit.

Because the receiver and barrel has been handled with hands there are brown spots due to the oils on your hands, its not rust. (its in the white) Its been inside a box in the back of a safe all its life.

This is what your build could look like:
http://www.atlanticfirearms.com/component/virtuemart/shipping-rifles/ak47-rifle-milled-by-liberty-arms-international-detail.html?Itemid=0
